29e9862c-6705-4040-ad9d-59f94e6d4c27.0ead96d3-41dc-41b7-a80d-ab163096df1c.description=
Runs multiple SSH command by creating an ssh shell and checking output against regular expressions

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
port - The port number for running the command. It overrides the port given inside the host input in a syntax like host\:port if used.
command - The commands to execute. This should be made up of 'send ' and 'expect ' statements separated by newlines.
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of user. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
privateKeyFile - Private key to be used during ssh authentication, relative to ICONCLUDE_HOME on RAS host.
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete.
newlineCharacters - The character sequence to send as the enter key being pressed after each 'send' statement as the send expect script is processed in the command input. Either '\r\n' '\n' '\r' or a comma delimited list of ASCII escape sequences.
characterDelay - The delay in milliseconds between sending characters of the SSH commands. 
characterSet - The characterSet name for input stream encoding from the target machine. For example, SJIS,EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8. 
sessionId - Identifier of a shared SSH shell session created by SSH Shell Logon. Instead of creating a new SSH shell session this one will be used if specified.

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Extra Results\:
visualized - The output of the command in XML format.
STDOUT - The STDOUT of the command.
29e9862c-6705-4040-ad9d-59f94e6d4c27.87a7d6a7-2669-459c-a6e8-6287ee0e0999.description=
This operation enables maintenance mode for the given Virtual Connect Domain Id. This operation will change the VCEM privileges on the VC Domain, allowing the user to change the domain configuration directly through Virtual Connect Manager and will update the VC Domain status to MAINTENANCE_MODE.

Inputs\:
    host - The VCEM hostname or IP address. 
    port - The VCEM port number. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input,  the default port is “50002”. Otherwise, the default port is “50001”.
Default values\: 50001, 50002
    username - The VCEM username. 
    password - The VCEM user's password. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input, this must be the keystore's password. 
    keystore - The local path of the keystore file. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input, logging on to VCEM will use a certificate. To learn how to set up the certificate, see the HP Virtual Connect Enterprise Manager Integration Guide. 
Value format\: C\:\Program Files\Hewlett-Packard\Operations Orchestration\jre1.6\lib\security\cacerts.
    vcDomainId - The VC Domain Id for which maintenance mode is to be enabled.
Examples\: 1, 2, 3

Results\:
    returnResult - The message indicating that status of the operation.  
 
Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong. See the HP Virtual Connect Enterprise Manager Integration Guide for troubleshooting help.

Notes\:
 
Prerequisites\:
1. Minimum role-based security required to run this operation is VCEM Group Administrator.
29e9862c-6705-4040-ad9d-59f94e6d4c27.93c41910-1cd5-4d19-a9e0-a35775b566a2.prompt=HostName\: 29e9862c-6705-4040-ad9d-59f94e6d4c27.d37eb26f-c70c-4671-bdc8-9e01c7813e85.description=DD Inputs\: list - The list of Switchipaddresses, followed with the Trunks (comma seperated) 
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.

This operation completes maintenance mode for the given Virtual Connect Domain Id. 

Inputs\:
    host - The VCEM hostname or IP address. 
    port - The VCEM port number. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input,  the default port is “50002”. Otherwise, the default port is “50001”.
Default values\: 50001, 50002
    username - The VCEM username. 
    password - The VCEM user's password. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input, this must be the keystore's password. 
    keystore - The local path of the keystore file. If you specify a value for the “keystore” input, logging on to VCEM will use a certificate. To learn how to set up the certificate, see the HP Virtual Connect Enterprise Manager Integration Guide. 
Value format\: C\:\Program Files\Hewlett-Packard\Operations Orchestration\jre1.6\lib\security\cacerts.
    vcDomainId - The VC Domain Id for which maintenance mode operation is to be completed.
Examples\: 1, 2, 3
    restoreConfig - If true and the new base configuration is not compatible with the current profile configuration, VCEM will restore the base configuration, overriding any changes done via VCM.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    async - Specifies whether to perform the task asynchronously. If you specify a value of “false”, the operation waits for the job to complete or time out if it reaches timeout. 
Valid values\: true, false
    timeout -  The time to wait in seconds before the operation is considered to have failed. If you specify a value of “true” for the “async” input, the “timeout” input value is ignored. 
Default value\: 180

Results\:
    returnResult - The message indicating that status of the operation.  
    retJobState - The state of the job. 
Examples\: COMPLETED, FAILED, PENDING, WARING or RUNNIG.
    retJsJobProgresses - A JavaScript Object string that contains the following information about the job progress if the operation fails or times out\:
        * retJobProcessDescription - The description of the last job progress. 
        * retJobProgressTime - The time of the last job progress.
        * retJobStartTime - The time that job started. 
        * retJobProgressPercent - The percent of the last job progress.      
Examples\: {"retJobProgressDescription"\:"Finished VC Domain Maintenance process.","retJobProgressTime"\:1314650420280,"retJobStartTime"\:1314650391947,"retJobProgressPercent"\:100}
 
Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong. See the HP Virtual Connect Enterprise Manager Integration Guide for troubleshooting help.

Notes\:
 
Prerequisites\:
1. Minimum role-based security required to run this operation is VCEM Group Administrator.
